Package: metayer
Title: tools for package development
Version: 0.2.4
Authors@R: 
    person("Dustin", "Lennon", , "dustin.lennon@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0002-8558-8765"))
Description: metayer is a collection of package development tools.  It aims to deliver an improved Jupyter
    experience; in particular, it provides machinery to produce uniform outputs across publishing context. A 
    second component of metayer is its integration of the cli and logger packages.  Use a cli method and have
    it piped into the logger with package-level context.  Use a wrapped cli method and enjoy package-level
    context in the log data.  metayer also provides: a global hierarchical storage container that leverages 
    native R environments; a with-style wrapper that facilitates temporary and safe monkey patching of 
    namespaced internals; and helper methods for inspecting function stack environments associated with dynamic
    scoping.
